  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Per JSON-RPC specification (https://www.jsonrpc.org/specification#request_object), the `id` property on a request object can be a `string`, `number`, or `null`.  Currently, Nethermind will respond with an incorrect JSON-RPC response object when it receives a request with a `null` `id` (see #1439 for example situation).\r\n\r\nI thought I fixed this in https://github.com/NethermindEth/nethermind/pull/1384, but it would appear that I actually made things worse.  ðŸ˜¢  Rather than blundering in the dark again, figured I would create a GitHub issue and let someone who knows what they are doing fix it instead.",
